/// Provenance graph endpoint.
///
/// Returns nodes (operations + artifacts) and edges for DAG visualization.
/// Node types: "operation" (primitives) and "artifact" (data files)
/// Edge types: "input" (artifact â†’ operation) and "output" (operation â†’ artifact)
async fn provenance_handler() -> impl IntoResponse {
    let manifest_path = session_manifest_path();

    if !manifest_path.exists() {
        return Json(serde_json::json!({
            "nodes": [],
            "edges": [],
            "error": "No session found"
        }));
    }

    match SessionManifest::load(&manifest_path) {
        Ok(manifest) => {
            let mut nodes = Vec::new();
            let mut edges = Vec::new();

            // Add operation nodes (only successful ones for cleaner graph)
            for op in &manifest.operations {
                if op.status != "success" {
                    continue;
                }

                nodes.push(serde_json::json!({
                    "id": op.id.to_string(),
                    "type": "operation",
                    "label": op.primitive,
                    "primitive": op.primitive,
                    "status": op.status,
                    "executed_at": op.executed_at.to_rfc3339(),
                    "duration_ms": op.duration_ms,
                    "summary": op.summary,
                }));

                // Add edges from input artifacts to this operation
                for input in &op.inputs {
                    edges.push(serde_json::json!({
                        "id": format!("{}->{}",input, op.id),
                        "source": input,
                        "target": op.id.to_string(),
                        "type": "input",
                    }));
                }

                // Add edges from this operation to output artifacts
                for output in &op.outputs {
                    edges.push(serde_json::json!({
                        "id": format!("{}->{}",op.id, output),
                        "source": op.id.to_string(),
                        "target": output,
                        "type": "output",
                    }));
                }
            }

            // Add artifact nodes
            for (filename, artifact) in &manifest.artifacts {
                nodes.push(serde_json::json!({
                    "id": filename,
                    "type": "artifact",
                    "label": filename,
                    "data_type": artifact.data_type,
                    "glance": artifact.glance,
                    "created_at": artifact.created_at.to_rfc3339(),
                }));
            }

            // Also add input files that aren't in artifacts (original uploads)
            let artifact_names: std::collections::HashSet<&String> =
                manifest.artifacts.keys().collect();

            for op in &manifest.operations {
                if op.status != "success" {
                    continue;
                }
                for input in &op.inputs {
                    if !artifact_names.contains(input) {
                        // Check if we already added this node
                        let already_added = nodes.iter().any(|n| {
                            n.get("id").and_then(|v| v.as_str()) == Some(input)
                        });
                        if !already_added {
                            nodes.push(serde_json::json!({
                                "id": input,
                                "type": "artifact",
                                "label": input,
                                "data_type": "Input",
                                "glance": "Original input file",
                                "created_at": null,
                            }));
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

            Json(serde_json::json!({
                "nodes": nodes,
                "edges": edges,
                "stats": {
                    "total_operations": manifest.operations.iter().filter(|o| o.status == "success").count(),
                    "total_artifacts": manifest.artifacts.len(),
                    "total_edges": edges.len(),
                }
            }))
        }
        Err(e) => Json(serde_json::json!({
            "nodes": [],
            "edges": [],
            "error": format!("Failed to load session: {}", e)
        })),
    }
}

export async function fetchOperations(options?: {
  limit?: number;
  offset?: number;
  status?: string;
  primitive?: string;
}): Promise<OperationsResponse> {
  try {
    const params = new URLSearchParams();
    if (options?.limit) params.set("limit", options.limit.toString());
    if (options?.offset) params.set("offset", options.offset.toString());
    if (options?.status) params.set("status", options.status);
    if (options?.primitive) params.set("primitive", options.primitive);

    const url = params.toString()
      ? `${DAEMON_URL}/operations?${params.toString()}`
      : `${DAEMON_URL}/operations`;

    const response = await fetch(url);
    if (!response.ok) {
      console.error("Failed to fetch operations:", response.statusText);
      return { operations: [], total: 0, limit: 100, offset: 0 };
    }
    return await response.json();
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error fetching operations:", error);
    return { operations: [], total: 0, limit: 100, offset: 0 };
  }
}

// Custom node for operations (primitives)
function OperationNode({ data }: { data: ProvenanceNode }) {
  return (
    <div className="px-3 py-2 bg-primary/20 border-2 border-primary rounded-lg min-w-[120px] text-center">
      <Handle type="target" position={Position.Top} className="!bg-primary" />
      <div className="flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
        <Play className="w-3 h-3 text-primary" />
        <span className="font-medium text-sm text-primary">{data.label}</span>

      {data.duration_ms !== undefined && (

      )}
      <Handle type="source" position={Position.Bottom} className="!bg-primary" />
    </div>
  );
}

// Custom node for artifacts (data files)
function ArtifactNode({ data }: { data: ProvenanceNode }) {
  const isInput = data.data_type === "Input";
  return (
    <div
      className={`px-3 py-2 border-2 rounded min-w-[100px] text-center ${
        isInput
          ? "bg-amber-500/20 border-amber-500"
          : "bg-secondary border-border"

    >
      <Handle type="target" position={Position.Top} className="!bg-muted-foreground" />

// Layout algorithm: simple layered layout
function layoutGraph(
  nodes: ProvenanceNode[],
  edges: ProvenanceEdge[]
): { nodes: Node[]; edges: Edge[] } {
  // Build adjacency for topological sort
  const nodeMap = new Map<string, ProvenanceNode>();
  const inDegree = new Map<string, number>();
  const outEdges = new Map<string, string[]>();

  nodes.forEach((n) => {
    nodeMap.set(n.id, n);
    inDegree.set(n.id, 0);
    outEdges.set(n.id, []);
  });

  edges.forEach((e) => {
    inDegree.set(e.target, (inDegree.get(e.target) || 0) + 1);
    outEdges.get(e.source)?.push(e.target);
  });

  // Topological sort with levels
  const levels: string[][] = [];
  let remaining = new Set(nodes.map((n) => n.id));

  while (remaining.size > 0) {
    const currentLevel: string[] = [];

    for (const id of remaining) {
      if (inDegree.get(id) === 0) {
        currentLevel.push(id);
      }
    }

    if (currentLevel.length === 0) {
      // Cycle detected or disconnected - just add remaining
      currentLevel.push(...remaining);
      remaining.clear();
    } else {
      for (const id of currentLevel) {
        remaining.delete(id);
        for (const target of outEdges.get(id) || []) {
          inDegree.set(target, (inDegree.get(target) || 0) - 1);
        }
      }
    }

    levels.push(currentLevel);
  }

  // Position nodes
  const LEVEL_HEIGHT = 120;
  const NODE_WIDTH = 180;
  const layoutedNodes: Node[] = [];

  levels.forEach((level, levelIndex) => {
    const levelWidth = level.length * NODE_WIDTH;
    const startX = -levelWidth / 2 + NODE_WIDTH / 2;

    level.forEach((id, nodeIndex) => {
      const node = nodeMap.get(id);
      if (!node) return;

      layoutedNodes.push({
        id,
        type: node.type,
        position: {
          x: startX + nodeIndex * NODE_WIDTH,
          y: levelIndex * LEVEL_HEIGHT,
        },
        data: node,
      });
    });
  });

  // Create edges
  const layoutedEdges: Edge[] = edges.map((e) => ({
    id: e.id,
    source: e.source,
    target: e.target,
    type: "smoothstep",
    animated: e.type === "output",
    style: {
      stroke: e.type === "input" ? "#6b7280" : "#3b82f6",
      strokeWidth: 2,
    },
    markerEnd: {
      type: MarkerType.ArrowClosed,
      color: e.type === "input" ? "#6b7280" : "#3b82f6",
    },
  }));

  return { nodes: layoutedNodes, edges: layoutedEdges };
}

export function ProvenanceTab() {
  const [graph, setGraph] = useState<ProvenanceGraph | null>(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [selectedNode, setSelectedNode] = useState<ProvenanceNode | null>(null);
  const [nodes, setNodes, onNodesChange] = useNodesState([]);
  const [edges, setEdges, onEdgesChange] = useEdgesState([]);

  const loadProvenance = useCallback(async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    const data = await fetchProvenance();
    setGraph(data);

    if (data.nodes.length > 0) {
      const { nodes: layoutedNodes, edges: layoutedEdges } = layoutGraph(
        data.nodes,
        data.edges
      );
      setNodes(layoutedNodes);
      setEdges(layoutedEdges);
    }

    setLoading(false);
  }, [setNodes, setEdges]);

  useEffect(() => {
    loadProvenance();
  }, [loadProvenance]);

  const onNodeClick = useCallback(
    (_: React.MouseEvent, node: Node) => {
      const provenanceNode = graph?.nodes.find((n) => n.id === node.id);
      setSelectedNode(provenanceNode || null);
    },
    [graph]
  );

  const stats = graph?.stats;

  if (loading && !graph) {
    return (
      <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center h-full gap-4 text-muted-foreground">
        <Loader2 className="w-8 h-8 animate-spin" />
        <p>Loading provenance graph...</p>
      </div>
    );
  }

  if (!graph || graph.nodes.length === 0) {
    return (
      <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center h-full gap-4 text-muted-foreground p-6">
        <GitBranch className="w-16 h-16" />
        <h2 className="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">Provenance Graph</h2>
        <p className="text-center max-w-md">
          No provenance data available. Run some primitives to see the data flow graph.
        </p>
        <button
          onClick={loadProvenance}
          className="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-primary-foreground rounded hover:bg-primary/90"
        >
          <RefreshCw className="w-4 h-4" />
          Refresh
        </button>
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col h-full">
      {/* Header */}
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 border-b border-border">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-4">
          <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
            <GitBranch className="w-5 h-5" />
            Provenance Graph
          </h2>
          {stats && (
            <div className="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
              <span>{stats.total_operations} operations</span>
              <span>&middot;</span>
              <span>{stats.total_artifacts} artifacts</span>
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
        <button
          onClick={loadProvenance}
          disabled={loading}
          className="flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 text-sm border border-border rounded hover:bg-accent disabled:opacity-50"
        >
          <RefreshCw className={`w-4 h-4 ${loading ? "animate-spin" : ""}`} />
          Refresh
        </button>
      </div>

      {/* Graph */}
      <div className="flex-1 relative">
        <ReactFlow
          nodes={nodes}
          edges={edges}
          onNodesChange={onNodesChange}
          onEdgesChange={onEdgesChange}
          onNodeClick={onNodeClick}
          nodeTypes={nodeTypes}
          fitView
          fitViewOptions={{ padding: 0.2 }}
          minZoom={0.1}
          maxZoom={2}
          className="bg-background"
        >
          <Background color="#374151" gap={20} />
          <Controls
            showInteractive={false}
            className="!bg-card !border-border !shadow-lg"
          />
        </ReactFlow>

        {/* Legend */}
        <div className="absolute bottom-4 left-4 bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-3 text-xs space-y-2">
          <div className="font-medium mb-2">Legend</div>
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
            <div className="w-4 h-3 bg-primary/20 border-2 border-primary rounded" />
            <span>Operation (primitive)</span>
          </div>
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
            <div className="w-4 h-3 bg-amber-500/20 border-2 border-amber-500 rounded" />
            <span>Input file</span>
          </div>
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
            <div className="w-4 h-3 bg-secondary border-2 border-border rounded" />
            <span>Output artifact</span>
          </div>
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mt-2 pt-2 border-t border-border">
            <div className="w-6 h-0.5 bg-muted-foreground" />
            <span>Data input</span>
          </div>
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
            <div className="w-6 h-0.5 bg-primary" />
            <span>Data output</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Node details panel */}
        {selectedNode && (
          <div className="absolute top-4 right-4 w-72 bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-4 shadow-lg">
            <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
              <h3 className="font-medium flex items-center gap-2">
                {selectedNode.type === "operation" ? (

                  <FileText className="w-4 h-4 text-muted-foreground" />

              <button
                onClick={() => setSelectedNode(null)}

    80â†’function layoutGraph(

    84â†’  // Build adjacency for topological sort

    94â†’
    95â†’  edges.forEach((e) => {

    97â†’    outEdges.get(e.source)?.push(e.target);
    98â†’  });
    99â†’
   100â†’  // Topological sort with levels
   101â†’  const levels: string[][] = [];
   102â†’  let remaining = new Set(nodes.map((n) => n.id));
   103â†’
   104â†’  while (remaining.size > 0) {
   105â†’    const currentLevel: string[] = [];
   106â†’
   107â†’    for (const id of remaining) {
   108â†’      if (inDegree.get(id) === 0) {

   110â†’      }
   111â†’    }
   112â†’

// Layout algorithm: simple layered layout
function layoutGraph(
  nodes: ProvenanceNode[],
  edges: ProvenanceEdge[]
): { nodes: Node[]; edges: Edge[] } {
  // Build adjacency for topological sort
  const nodeMap = new Map<string, ProvenanceNode>();
  const inDegree = new Map<string, number>();
  const outEdges = new Map<string, string[]>();

  nodes.forEach((n) => {
    nodeMap.set(n.id, n);
    inDegree.set(n.id, 0);
    outEdges.set(n.id, []);
  });

  edges.forEach((e) => {
    inDegree.set(e.target, (inDegree.get(e.target) || 0) + 1);
    outEdges.get(e.source)?.push(e.target);
  });

  // Topological sort with levels
  const levels: string[][] = [];
  let remaining = new Set(nodes.map((n) => n.id));

  while (remaining.size > 0) {
    const currentLevel: string[] = [];

    // Use Array.from for Set iteration (TypeScript compatibility)
    for (const id of Array.from(remaining)) {
      if (inDegree.get(id) === 0) {
        currentLevel.push(id);
      }
    }

    if (currentLevel.length === 0) {
      // Cycle detected or disconnected - just add remaining
      currentLevel.push(...Array.from(remaining));
      remaining.clear();
    } else {
      for (const id of currentLevel) {
        remaining.delete(id);
        for (const target of outEdges.get(id) || []) {
          inDegree.set(target, (inDegree.get(target) || 0) - 1);
        }
      }
    }

    levels.push(currentLevel);
  }

  // Position nodes
  const LEVEL_HEIGHT = 120;
  const NODE_WIDTH = 180;
  const layoutedNodes: Node[] = [];

  levels.forEach((level, levelIndex) => {
    const levelWidth = level.length * NODE_WIDTH;
    const startX = -levelWidth / 2 + NODE_WIDTH / 2;

    level.forEach((id, nodeIndex) => {
      const node = nodeMap.get(id);
      if (!node) return;

      layoutedNodes.push({
        id,
        type: node.type,
        position: {
          x: startX + nodeIndex * NODE_WIDTH,
          y: levelIndex * LEVEL_HEIGHT,
        },
        data: { ...node } as Record<string, unknown>,
      });
    });
  });

  // Create edges
  const layoutedEdges: Edge[] = edges.map((e) => ({
    id: e.id,
    source: e.source,
    target: e.target,
    type: "smoothstep",
    animated: e.type === "output",
    style: {
      stroke: e.type === "input" ? "#6b7280" : "#3b82f6",
      strokeWidth: 2,
    },
    markerEnd: {
      type: MarkerType.ArrowClosed,
      color: e.type === "input" ? "#6b7280" : "#3b82f6",
    },
  }));

  return { nodes: layoutedNodes, edges: layoutedEdges };
}

// Layout algorithm using dagre for proper graph layout
function layoutGraph(
  nodes: ProvenanceNode[],
  edges: ProvenanceEdge[]
): { nodes: Node[]; edges: Edge[] } {
  // Create a new dagre graph
  const dagreGraph = new dagre.graphlib.Graph();
  dagreGraph.setDefaultEdgeLabel(() => ({}));

  // Configure the layout
  dagreGraph.setGraph({
    rankdir: "TB", // Top to bottom
    nodesep: 80,   // Horizontal spacing between nodes
    ranksep: 100,  // Vertical spacing between ranks
    marginx: 50,
    marginy: 50,
  });

  // Add nodes to the dagre graph
  const nodeMap = new Map<string, ProvenanceNode>();
  nodes.forEach((node) => {
    nodeMap.set(node.id, node);
    // Adjust width based on label length
    const labelWidth = Math.max(NODE_WIDTH, node.label.length * 10 + 60);
    dagreGraph.setNode(node.id, {
      width: labelWidth,
      height: NODE_HEIGHT
    });
  });

  // Add edges to the dagre graph
  edges.forEach((edge) => {
    dagreGraph.setEdge(edge.source, edge.target);
  });

  // Run the layout algorithm
  dagre.layout(dagreGraph);

  // Extract positions from dagre and create React Flow nodes
  const layoutedNodes: Node[] = nodes.map((node) => {
    const dagreNode = dagreGraph.node(node.id);
    return {
      id: node.id,
      type: node.type,
      position: {
        // Dagre gives center positions, adjust to top-left for React Flow
        x: dagreNode.x - (dagreNode.width || NODE_WIDTH) / 2,
        y: dagreNode.y - NODE_HEIGHT / 2,
      },
      data: { ...node } as Record<string, unknown>,
    };
  });

  // Create edges with styling
  const layoutedEdges: Edge[] = edges.map((e) => ({
    id: e.id,
    source: e.source,
    target: e.target,
    type: "smoothstep",
    animated: e.type === "output",
    style: {
      stroke: e.type === "input" ? "#6b7280" : "#3b82f6",
      strokeWidth: 2,
    },
    markerEnd: {
      type: MarkerType.ArrowClosed,
      color: e.type === "input" ? "#6b7280" : "#3b82f6",
    },
  }));

  return { nodes: layoutedNodes, edges: layoutedEdges };
}

export function ProvenanceTab() {
  const [graph, setGraph] = useState<ProvenanceGraph | null>(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [selectedNode, setSelectedNode] = useState<ProvenanceNode | null>(null);
  const [nodes, setNodes, onNodesChange] = useNodesState<Node>([]);
  const [edges, setEdges, onEdgesChange] = useEdgesState<Edge>([]);

  // Apply layout to current graph data
  const applyLayout = useCallback(() => {
    if (graph && graph.nodes.length > 0) {
      const { nodes: layoutedNodes, edges: layoutedEdges } = layoutGraph(
        graph.nodes,
        graph.edges
      );
      setNodes(layoutedNodes);
      setEdges(layoutedEdges);
    }
  }, [graph, setNodes, setEdges]);

  // Load provenance data and apply layout
  const loadProvenance = useCallback(async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    const data = await fetchProvenance();
    setGraph(data);

    if (data.nodes.length > 0) {
      const { nodes: layoutedNodes, edges: layoutedEdges } = layoutGraph(
        data.nodes,
        data.edges
      );
      setNodes(layoutedNodes);
      setEdges(layoutedEdges);
